/*!
    \title qtlottieviewer Example
    \example qtlottieviewer
    \image qtlottieviewerexample.png
    \brief An example demonstrating the use of Qt LottieAnimation in an application.
    \ingroup qtlottieexamples
    \examplecategory {Graphics}

    This example demonstrates how to use the \l{LottieAnimation} item
    of the \l{Qt.labs.lottieqt} module to directly display and control
    a Lottie animated vector graphics file in a Qt Quick application.

    \section1 Overview

    The main part of the example window is a Rectangle containing a
    LottieAnimation item which plays a Lottie animation.

    Below this is a row controls. The user can control the animation
    speed with the Frame Rate slider, and zoom in and out using the
    Scale slider. The animation can be stopped and restarted using the
    Play/Pause button. When paused, the user can select the exact
    frame to be displayed using the Goto Frame slider. The Open button
    will display a file dialog, allowing the user to select a Lottie
    file to load and display.

    LottieAnimation is a \l{QQuickPaintedItem}, employing software
    rasterization of the vector graphics. For alternative ways
    displaying Lottie files in Quick applications, utilizing graphics
    hardware rendering, see \l{lottietoqml} and the \l{VectorImage}
    item.

*/
